---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import UtilityBar from '../components/UtilityBar.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import StickyMobileCTA from '../components/StickyMobileCTA.astro';
import DisclosureBlock from '../components/DisclosureBlock.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { SITE_URL, BRAND_LEGAL } from '../config';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About DenverJunkHelp.com | How This Site Works"
  description="DenverJunkHelp.com is a local quote and referral website for junk removal in the Denver area. Learn how the site works, what we do, and what we don't."
  canonical={`${SITE_URL}/about/`}
>
  <UtilityBar />
  <Header />
  <main class="flex-1 w-full" aria-label="Main content">

    <div class="bg-card border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <Breadcrumbs items={[
          { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
          { label: 'About' },
        ]} />
        <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-foreground mb-6">
          About DenverJunkHelp.com
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
          A practical, local resource for figuring out junk removal in the Denver metro area &mdash; and for getting connected with a local provider when you need one.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="py-16 px-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <article class="prose prose-lg prose-headings:font-serif max-w-none text-muted-foreground">
        <h2>What this site is</h2>
        <p>
          DenverJunkHelp.com is a small, locally-focused information and quote-request site. We
          publish straightforward guides about junk removal in Denver and the surrounding
          metro area &mdash; what the city's free pickup program covers, when you actually
          need a private hauler, what affects pricing, and what to ask before booking.
        </p>
        <p>
          We also run a simple quote-request form. If you fill it out, we can forward your
          details to an independent local junk removal provider who serves Denver and may
          contact you about pricing, availability, and next steps.
        </p>

        <h2>What this site is not</h2>
        <p>
          We want to be upfront: {BRAND_LEGAL} is not a junk removal company. We do not own
          trucks, employ crews, hold a hauling license, or carry hauling insurance. We do
          not perform pickups, disposal, or recycling ourselves.
        </p>
        <p>
          The independent local provider who responds to your request is the one who
          actually does the work &mdash; and they are the one you should ask about
          licensing, insurance, pricing, scheduling, and anything else specific to the
          job.
        </p>

        <h2>Why we built it</h2>
        <p>
          Most "junk removal Denver" search results push you straight to a phone number or
          a one-line booking widget. That works for people who already know what they need.
          It doesn't help the person who's trying to figure out whether to wait for the
          city truck, whether they can put a refrigerator on the curb, or whether their
          job is closer to a single-item pickup or a full cleanout.
        </p>
        <p>
          We wanted a calmer, more useful place to start: clear guides, honest pricing
          context, and a no-pressure way to request a quote when a private hauler is
          actually the right call.
        </p>

        <h2>How we make money</h2>
        <p>
          When this site eventually has steady traffic, it may earn revenue from a
          referral relationship with one or more local junk removal providers, or from
          advertising. None of that affects the editorial content. Our goal is to help
          you make a good decision &mdash; including telling you when the right answer is
          to wait for the city truck and pay nothing.
        </p>

        <h2>How to reach us</h2>
        <p>
          The fastest way to get a quote is the{' '}
          <a href="/contact/" class="text-primary hover:underline font-medium">quote request form</a>.
          For questions about the site itself, see the email address in the footer.
        </p>
      </article>

      <div class="mt-12">
        <DisclosureBlock />
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <Footer />
  <StickyMobileCTA />
</BaseLayout>
